Saif Qaddafi Probed by LSE Over Plagiarism Claim, Sky News Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-03-02T07:39:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/saif-qaddafi-probed-by-lse-over-plagiarism-claim-sky-news-says.html
Saif Qaddafi, the son of Libyan
leader  Muammar Qaddafi , is being investigated by the  London
School of Economics  over claims he plagiarised material for his
PhD thesis, Sky News reported, citing the college.  Saif Qaddafi studied at the LSE between 2003 and 2008,
gaining a Master of Science degree as well as a PhD; the LSE
said it was investigating claims that he had plagiarised
sections of his thesis and employed a ghost writer, the news
channel said.    To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Chris Peterson  at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  